  "title": "ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Site Supervision:</strong>Oversee daily construction activities including track laying, ballast work, sleepers, rail welding, tamping, drainage, and civil structures.Ensure works are executed in line with approved drawings, method statements, and project specifications.</li><li><strong>Planning & Coordination:</strong>Coordinate with subcontractors, suppliers, and consultants to ensure timely progress of works.Monitor resources (manpower, equipment, and materials) to achieve planned targets.</li><li><strong>Quality Control & Documentation:</strong>Conduct site inspections and ensure compliance with project quality requirements.Prepare and maintain daily site reports, inspection requests, material approvals, and as-built documentation.Support testing and commissioning activities.</li><li><strong>Health, Safety & Environment (HSE):</strong>Ensure compliance with all safety regulations and project-specific HSE requirements.Conduct toolbox talks and promotes a safety-first culture at the site.</li><li><strong>Technical Support:</strong>Assist in resolving technical issues on-site in coordination with the engineering/design team.Review and interpret construction drawings, technical specifications, and standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree/Diploma in Civil Engineering, Railway Engineering, or related discipline.</li><li>3 years of site experience in railway infrastructure projects (track, civil, or systems).</li><li>Knowledge of railway construction methodologies, track geometry, tamping, and welding processes.</li><li>Familiarity with international and local railway standards (AREMA, EN, BS, SS, etc.) is an advantage.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office, AutoCAD, and project management tools.</li><li>Strong problem-solving, leadership, and communication skills.</li></ul>",
